.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-media_convert \- Batch convert images and videos to modern formats, optionally stripping EXIF metadata from images and compressing video output using ffmpeg.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility media_convert
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Batch convert images and videos to modern formats, optionally stripping EXIF metadata from images and compressing video output using ffmpeg.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBImage conversion\fP — converts PNG, JPG, JPEG, and WebP files using ImageMagick or ffmpeg
.IP \(bu 4
\fBVideo conversion\fP — converts MP4, MOV, MKV, and AVI files using ffmpeg with libx264
.IP \(bu 4
\fBEXIF stripping\fP — removes location, camera, and timestamp metadata from images
.IP \(bu 4
\fBQuality control\fP — configurable output quality for image conversion
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDirectory scanning\fP — recursively finds all matching files in a source directory
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDry-run by default\fP — previews conversions without writing any files
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided setup prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind image --to webp ~/Pictures

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind image --to webp --apply ~/Pictures

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind image --to webp --quality 85 --strip-exif --apply ~/Pictures

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind image --to jpg --apply ./photo.png

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind video --to mp4 --apply ~/Videos

bash _media_convert/_media_convert.sh --kind image --to webp --output ~/converted --apply ~/Pictures
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fCPATH...\fP   |   Source file or directory to convert
\fC--kind image\  |  video\fP   |   Type of media to convert (default: \fCimage\fP)
\fC--to FORMAT\fP   |   Target format extension (default: \fCwebp\fP for image, \fCmp4\fP for video)
\fC--quality N\fP   |   Output quality for images, 1–100 (default: \fC82\fP)
\fC--strip-exif\fP   |   Strip EXIF metadata from image output
\fC--output DIR\fP   |   Directory to write converted files to (default: \fC./converted_<kind>\fP)
\fC--apply\fP   |   Execute conversions (dry-run preview if omitted)
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH SUPPORTED FORMATS
.PP
.SS Image input formats
\fCpng\fP, \fCjpg\fP, \fCjpeg\fP, \fCwebp\fP
.PP
.SS Image output formats
Format   |   Notes
\fCwebp\fP   |   Best size/quality ratio, modern browsers and apps
\fCjpg\fP   |   Universal compatibility
\fCpng\fP   |   Lossless, larger file size
.PP
.SS Video input formats
\fCmp4\fP, \fCmov\fP, \fCmkv\fP, \fCavi\fP
.PP
.SS Video output formats
Format   |   Notes
\fCmp4\fP   |   Widest compatibility, uses libx264
\fCmkv\fP   |   Open container format
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH CONVERSION BACKENDS
.PP
Kind   |   Primary tool   |   Fallback
Image   |   \fCmagick\fP (ImageMagick)   |   \fCffmpeg\fP
Video   |   \fCffmpeg\fP   |   None — required
.PP
Video conversion always requires \fCffmpeg\fP. Image conversion uses ImageMagick when available for better quality control and EXIF stripping support.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OUTPUT LOCATION
.PP
Converted files are written to the output directory using the original filename with the new extension:
.PP
.EX
~/Pictures/holiday.jpg  →  ./converted_image/holiday.webp
~/Videos/demo.mov       →  ./converted_video/demo.mp4
.EE
.PP
Original files are never modified or deleted.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   No source paths given, or required tool not installed
